==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Liquefy
<hw>Liq"ue*fy</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧k"w⟦esl⟧*f⟦imac⟧)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Liquefied</conjf>
<pr>(-f⟦imac⟧d)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Liquefying</conjf> <pr>(-f⟦imac⟧`⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[F. <ets>liqu⟦eacute⟧fier</ets>, L. <ets>liquere</ets> to be liquid
+ <ets>facere</ets>, <ets>-ficare</ets> (in comp.), to make. See
<er>Liquid</er>, and <er>-fy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To convert
from a solid form to that of a liquid; to melt; to dissolve; and
technically, to melt by the sole agency of heat.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To convert from a gaseous form into a liquid;
<as>as, to liquefy natural gas</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Liquefy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Liquefy
<hw>Liq"ue*fy</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become liquid.</def>
<wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Liquescency</ent>⟦br⟧
